premise_source_doc_sentence: Dawn  (  from an Old English verb dagian `` to become day ''  )  or astronomical dawn is the time that marks , depending on the specific usage , the beginning of the twilight before sunrise , the period of the pre-sunrise twilight or the time of sunrise .
When identified as the beginning of or the period of twilight , it is recognized by the presence of weak sunlight , while the Sun itself is still below the horizon .
